commit_message:
Use sum of volumes and snapshots for cinder usage

The cinder quota on gigabytes is the sum of both volumes and snapshots,
therefore in the horizon view we should be representing usage as the
combination of volumes and snapshots, otherwise users will be confused
when getting quota errors on volume or snapshot creation.

Closes-Bug: 1513179
Change-Id: Id23e0dd3a3f810e75f9013cecbf8a826c97e34c6
(cherry picked from commit 944c8bafdcf12d0a0dd56c6c43eab84f513d6e5f)

commit_message:
Add self.raid for iSCSI based drivers

This commit adds self.raid = agent.AgentRAID()
for the drivers pxe_ipmitool, pxe_ipminative, pxe_ssh,
pxe_ilo, pxe_vbox. The same was done for agent drivers in
Ifa640d4839b2f08410ceec57c2972e2f9dc69db3.

It also adds test cases for these drivers which were
missing.

Change-Id: I5e7046ec56dd851a197da8571bd933cabd3dd210
Implements: blueprint inband-raid-configuration

commit_message:
Fix /NetworkDriver.CreateEndpoint validation

In Interface properties, Address and AddressIPv6 are coming as empty
strings from libnetwork and that is breaking current validation logic.
Logic is added to accept empty string also for mac and ipv4 address.

Change-Id: Ib32bee76c6add1c5af616b7d74b346eef906fa8b
Closes-Bug: #1507508

commit_message:
Add a note to docs about parameter defaults

Document that the client will now use most defaults from the Heat
templates, rather than be hardcoded in the client. Environment files
are the proper way to override these defaults.

commit_message:
Workaround a dispute between osc and neutronclient

python-openstackclient wants network_api_version to be 2. neutronclient
wants it to be 2.0. There is a patch to OSC to make it understand both,
but in the mean time, let's unbreak people.

Change-Id: I4d8f187d1302c5bcfa246e017e6c6d8af9c3f733

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-11-05 04:28:22.000000000', 'files': ['labs/osbash/tools/restore-cluster.sh'], 'message': 'restore-cluster: skip non-existent VMs

The restore-cluster.sh tool aborts if a VM from VM_LIST does not exist.
Therefore, the script breaks if the cluster building never managed to
create all VMs in the list.

This patch lets the script skip non-existent VMs.

Change-Id: I0e0fd2dea9f582f1def0f734f10e4656d98394c6
'}]
commit_message:
restore-cluster: skip non-existent VMs

The restore-cluster.sh tool aborts if a VM from VM_LIST does not exist.
Therefore, the script breaks if the cluster building never managed to
create all VMs in the list.

This patch lets the script skip non-existent VMs.

Change-Id: I0e0fd2dea9f582f1def0f734f10e4656d98394c6

commit_message:
Add custom package apt provides with timeout

It may be that dkpg database is locked by abother process during
the Puppet run. Consequently, the deployment will fail.
To mitigate the issue, it is possible to wrap default apt provider
with a class which waits until the lock is released or timeout
expired.

Change-Id: I691ca96cced232483fb2f3e79cbf3ee402f765ea
Fixes-bug: #1510107

commit_message:
Workaround for int value with verbose_level

python-openstackclient uses an int value for verbose level which the
stringification patch broke. As a quick fix, special case verbose_level,
as fixing it properly might take more than 5 minutes.

Change-Id: Ie12a40d3d3e400b3ec2103d7a58c4902fb10fc2d
Closes-Bug: #1513919

commit_message:
Read vif port information in bulk

During startup, the agent was making many calls per port
to read information about the current VLAN, external ID, etc.
This resulted in hundreds of calls just to read information about
a relatively small number of ports.

This patch addresses that by converting a few key functions to
lookup information for all of the ports at once.

Performance improvement on dev laptop for 250 ports from agent
start to port ACTIVE status:
   before: 1m21s
   after: 1m06s

Closes-Bug: #1460233
Change-Id: Ic80c85a07fee3e5651dc19819c6cebdc2048dda7
(cherry pick-picked from commit 4dc68ea88bf4f07b13253bf9eeedffe22b1f8013)
Conflicts:
	neutron/agent/common/ovs_lib.py
	neutron/plugins/openvswitch/agent/ovs_neutron_agent.py
	neutron/tests/unit/plugins/ml2/drivers/openvswitch/agent/test_ovs_neutron_agent.py

to report or handle the exception based the code.

commit_message:
Disable command run under root user

Running openstack command with python-tripleoclient under
root user is not supported and should not be allowed. Added
check for user and exit if it is root (EUID=0) to openstack
undercloud install command.

Each command can be disabled for root by adding
utils.ensure_run_as_normal_user() into it's body.

Backport to stable/liberty of Change-Id: I685c639e02790483d1607c7eac038f8b9b8dc99e

Change-Id: I374a27ff4c7a16eb42dd474a7978a953aa9dbb80
Closes-Bug: rhbz#1239088

commit_message:
Really get the "general" packages

We are specifying the argument to get_packages incorrectly, so we are
not actually adding the packages in "general" to the list of packages.

In most cases, this is hidden as other more specific plugins/services
request their packages.  However, as
I2dafd32f211fcbc9fff53030d736d97a5f1bb2df shows, not always.  I think
this was uncovered by 5f8133caac097235ed4fe73d878df0ee907eb51c

Change-Id: Ie1b8d09369281059d21da61b2725a457f708ae9e

subject: Add common info to the REST debugging log
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-09-02 05:32:14.000000000', 'files': ['tempest_lib/common/rest_client.py'], 'message': "Add common info to the REST debugging log

Current REST debugging log doesn't contain common info like status
code, http method and URL. They are output as the info log, and in
most case the info log is output just before the debugging log.
Developers can know the combination of them usually, but sometimes
it is difficult to know because the tests run in parallel.
This patch adds common info to the debugging log for knowing the
combination surelly.

Change-Id: I8c395384203fca4d842bcc117d221a227fa080f8
"}]
commit_message:
Add common info to the REST debugging log

Current REST debugging log doesn't contain common info like status
code, http method and URL. They are output as the info log, and in
most case the info log is output just before the debugging log.
Developers can know the combination of them usually, but sometimes
it is difficult to know because the tests run in parallel.
This patch adds common info to the debugging log for knowing the
combination surelly.

Change-Id: I8c395384203fca4d842bcc117d221a227fa080f8

Update Octavia release model

Since Octavia is now the default reference implementation of LBaaS
V2, add the following tags to it:

- release:cycle-with-milestones
- release:has-stable-branches

We'll run this way for a single cycle and then try to move to
"release:managed" during Nxxx.

commit_message:
Do not resolve keystone values if it is None

In patch Ic7a3001ab271cad12f4fe45c0930562070a0d600 were added new
functions for resolving keystone values. However it may lead to an error,
when the user does not specify the related property and it's None.
These functions can not resolve None value and fail.
This patch adds check for None values.

Change-Id: I667e61e9553a92703dbc5a37a311d93c4a377d4b
Closes-Bug: #1509354

commit_message:
Add python-memcached to list of installed pkgs on controllers

We use memcached for a few services but can't rely on the python
module being installed as a dependency because it techincally isn't
needed unless one configures the services to use memcached.

More at: https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1271433#c12

Change-Id: I462532ca49157b57b4a558922bd3cb2cbce103e6

[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-06-05 10:00:36.000000000', 'files': ['neutron/plugins/ml2/drivers/type_tunnel.py'], 'message': "Log a new tunnel endpoint being registered or updated

Sometimes we'd like to know why some tunnels are not created on a node.
It may be either an agent failing to report its (new) local_ip, or
server failing to notify other parties about a new endpoint to create.

To understand whether an agent actually hit the controller, it would be
great to have a (non-debug) logging message just for that on controller
side.

It should be fine to log new or existing agent updates in non-debug
log level since those events are not too often, so we should not expect
logs being flooded.

The patch adds to a debug log for _add_endpoint, logging with info level
when an agent is registered or updated.  It also reports the host name
and tunnel type in addition to IP address, and distinguishes between the
cases of a new, unknown, agent being registered, and an existing one
being updated.

Change-Id: I9b5f52db119d48078612b4c3d42e996d172a2dff
"}]
commit_message:
Log a new tunnel endpoint being registered or updated

Sometimes we'd like to know why some tunnels are not created on a node.
It may be either an agent failing to report its (new) local_ip, or
server failing to notify other parties about a new endpoint to create.

To understand whether an agent actually hit the controller, it would be
great to have a (non-debug) logging message just for that on controller
side.

It should be fine to log new or existing agent updates in non-debug
log level since those events are not too often, so we should not expect
logs being flooded.

The patch adds to a debug log for _add_endpoint, logging with info level
when an agent is registered or updated.  It also reports the host name
and tunnel type in addition to IP address, and distinguishes between the
cases of a new, unknown, agent being registered, and an existing one
being updated.

Change-Id: I9b5f52db119d48078612b4c3d42e996d172a2dff

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-11-08 04:00:23.000000000', 'files': ['openstack_requirements/cmds/generate.py', 'openstack_requirements/tests/test_generate.py'], 'message': 'Deal with underscores in blacklist during generate-constraints

In change id  I60adf0dca4aa32f4ef6bca61250b375c8a3703c6, we added
flake8_docstrings to the black list. However as seen in
I8bfff1b2e65541959e7f2ae0fa6ca6c17889eb54, the generate-constraints
job ends up proposing adding "flake8-docstrings===0.2.1.post1" to
the upper-constraints.txt. This is because of the '-' vs '_'
difference. So just like in Ibaa22657a2cf2c0ad96dbd0b9bc43cdafe6a1d56,

'}]
commit_message:
Deal with underscores in blacklist during generate-constraints

In change id  I60adf0dca4aa32f4ef6bca61250b375c8a3703c6, we added
flake8_docstrings to the black list. However as seen in
I8bfff1b2e65541959e7f2ae0fa6ca6c17889eb54, the generate-constraints
job ends up proposing adding "flake8-docstrings===0.2.1.post1" to
the upper-constraints.txt. This is because of the '-' vs '_'
difference. So just like in Ibaa22657a2cf2c0ad96dbd0b9bc43cdafe6a1d56,
we need to convert the items in black list to the correct safe name
before trying to check if the item is in the black list.

Change-Id: Ieb1cd44e908b80d58a20bf0d0e1e6b10f17ae95e

commit_message:
Fix dockerctl unlocking

* replace $FDLOCK with correct file descriptor
* do an unlock before attaching to a container – it never exits unless
  killed by supervisord
* correctly redirect error message to stderr
* remove /var/lock/dockerctl

Closes-bug: 1513422
Change-Id: Idd70c381632e3dca7c24edab78a731dc03f363e1

commit_message:
Enable "openstack server pause" command to take multiple servers.

Current "openstack server pause" command could only pause one server.
Improve it to be able to handle more than one servers. Also improve
the doc to reflect the new feature.

Change-Id: I809f77f0720457c9cdc1028a70b391c75885984c
Implements: blueprint cmd-with-multi-servers

commit_message:
Disable --save-only mode during post-deployment

It is common for users to run bootstrap_admin_node to apply
a patch to Fuel Master, which has the side effect of calling
fuelmenu --save-only --iface=ethN. This behavior initializes
all fields to defaults, which has negative consequences.

Now fuelmenu --save-only --iface=ethN will result in a message
saying that the user should run full fuelmenu in order to make
changes.

Moved get_deployment_mode to common.utils so it can be called
from save_only without expensive urwid imports.

Added unit tests for get_deployment_mode

Change-Id: I78d3261a5e2700b7533d9873f6bec9cc4e98c362
Closes-Bug: #1513486

revisions:
[{'number': 8, 'created': '2015-11-08 22:56:24.000000000', 'files': ['openstack_dashboard/contrib/sahara/content/data_processing/cluster_templates/tests.py', 'openstack_dashboard/dashboards/admin/metering/tests.py', 'openstack_dashboard/dashboards/admin/aggregates/tests.py', 'horizon/tables/base.py', 'openstack_dashboard/dashboards/project/containers/views.py', 'openstack_dashboard/dashboards/project/containers/tests.py', 'openstack_dashboard/contrib/sahara/content/data_processing/clusters/tests.py', 'tox.ini', 'openstack_dashboard/test/test_data/swift_data.py'], 'message': "py3: Fix unicode versus bytes issues

* DataTable: don't try to decode Unicode from UTF-8. Only decode on
  Python 2.
* Use oslo_serialization.jsonutils.dump_as_bytes() to encode JSON

"}]
commit_message:
py3: Fix unicode versus bytes issues

* DataTable: don't try to decode Unicode from UTF-8. Only decode on
  Python 2.
* Use oslo_serialization.jsonutils.dump_as_bytes() to encode JSON
  as bytes.
* Use oslo_serialization.jsonutils.loads() instead of json.loads() to
  accept bytes string as input. On Python 3, json.loads() only
  accepts Unicode string.
* Fix unit tests: HTTP body type is bytes.
* Container tests: use a named temporary file, the function handling
  the filename fails. On Python 3, TemporaryFile() uses a number for
  the filename: the file descriptor.
* Don't encode filename to UTF-8 on Python 3, keep Unicode.
* tox.ini: add 2 admin tests on Python 3.4.

Partial-Implements: blueprint porting-python3
Change-Id: Ib7e2cb17f20474590fac18faf8116131692ad694

[IBP] remove '-F' flag from resize2fs command

'-F' flag is unnecessary and causes failures in case of
using vagrant environment.

commit_message:
Rename .jsx files to .js

Since we use Babel to transform JSX and Webpack for bundling,
ti doesn't make sense anymore to keep a separate .jsx extension
for files.

Change-Id: If70b512d7a27684d2b9b84b24f19658294cc1505

Disable py34 for networking-cisco kilo and juno

Stable kilo and juno did not support python 3.4 so there is no point
testing it against those branches. This is blocking patches merging
into our stable branches.

subject: Fix race condition with router creation
revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2015-11-09 09:27:55.000000000', 'files': ['requirements.txt', 'murano/common/exceptions.py', 'murano/engine/system/net_explorer.py'], 'message': 'Fix race condition with router creation

Previously when murano deployed a bunch of environments from scratch
it was possible to have an error during router creation. Router was
created by env_1 and before it was fully configure it was accessed by
env_2 and then the error occurred.

Change-Id: I6936a2c46bf41c68e4aceca4a333723a27165071
Closes-Bug: #1493883
'}]
commit_message:
Fix race condition with router creation

Previously when murano deployed a bunch of environments from scratch
it was possible to have an error during router creation. Router was
created by env_1 and before it was fully configure it was accessed by
env_2 and then the error occurred.

Change-Id: I6936a2c46bf41c68e4aceca4a333723a27165071
Closes-Bug: #1493883

commit_message:
Add CLI tests for environment redeploy

- Added test that checks that it is possible to add app to the
deployed environment and redeploy it
- Added test that checks that it is possible to delete app from
the deployed environment and redeploy it
- Compose neeeded for deployment steps in the one method called
'deploy_environment' to avoid code duplication
- Added 'generate_uuid' method for application id generation

Partially implements: blueprint cli-tests-coverage-improvement

Change-Id: I6cbc718efa0d4eb0c5128b7a1d9637c386acbc74

commit_message:
Incorrect parsed variable name

database_user_create was not correctly referenced when parsing the
variable names. This could never actually lead to a situation that
reported a false change, but it could break an operation if you were
using the --step option with ansible and skipped the database create
task.

TrivialFix
Backport: Liberty

Change-Id: Idf69fffcc3814f509448ccea11b7d175f074ccf1

subject: Add dsvm into job names for Kolla
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-11-07 17:53:57.000000000', 'files': ['jenkins/jobs/kolla.yaml', 'zuul/openstack_functions.py', 'jenkins/jobs/projects.yaml', 'zuul/layout.yaml'], 'message': "Add dsvm into job names for Kolla

clarkb suggested dsvm be in the job names for Kolla to follow the
job naming convention. In the case of the experimental job we have
recently merged, that it as a requirement for the name of the job.

To keep consistency within the project and within the OpenStack
community we are renaming all of the gates that use the dsvm's to the
convention that all other jobnames follow.

Since the tox paramaters do not change in the jobs/kolla.yaml, this
requires no change on the Kolla side.

Change-Id: I9a22434d99b4deb7936ecaf7b714d0dc41666367
"}]
commit_message:
Add dsvm into job names for Kolla

clarkb suggested dsvm be in the job names for Kolla to follow the
job naming convention. In the case of the experimental job we have
recently merged, that it as a requirement for the name of the job.

To keep consistency within the project and within the OpenStack
community we are renaming all of the gates that use the dsvm's to the
convention that all other jobnames follow.

Since the tox paramaters do not change in the jobs/kolla.yaml, this
requires no change on the Kolla side.

Change-Id: I9a22434d99b4deb7936ecaf7b714d0dc41666367

commit_message:
Introduce Murano extended logging class

There is a range of extended logging options in Openstack services that use
openstack.common.logger (Ceilometer, Cinder, Heat, Keystone, Nova).
Adding murano::logging to support them like it done for puppet-heat,
puppet-ceilometer, puppet-cinder, etc.

Change-Id: I0139cff7ae729381ffb2f9535fa74912d54fa4af

commit_message:
Allowing shares to be edited on cluster update

In order to allow the shares to be updated on a running

commit_message:
Add functional api tests for categories

- Added positive and negative tempest api tests for work with
categories
- Change inheritance: made separate class for authorisation, made
separate class that will contain methods for object creation (and
cleanup for them). Lately all methods for object creation will be
moved to this class and will use right cleanup mechanism (instead of
current implementation when objects save in array). This change was
made in this commit to avoid using incorrect solution in new tests.

Implements: blueprint tempest-tests-for-categories-management

subject: Add kolla-mesos deliverable repo to Kolla
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-11-02 10:18:42.000000000', 'files': ['reference/projects.yaml'], 'message': 'Add kolla-mesos deliverable repo to Kolla

The kolla-mesos repository was majority voted accepted by the core
reviewer team of Kolla to be adopted into the Kolla governance.
The purpose of this repository is to orchestrate a Kolla deployment
in addition to Ansible but instead with Mesos.  If this experiment
fails, the repository will be filed in the attic.

The core reviewer team has committed to reviewing the changes for
this repository and learning how mesos operates.  Angus Salkeld
of Mirantis has committed 4 full time engineers to work on this
project.

The structure of the governance will be the addition of a team
kolla-mesos-core with only 2 people from Mirantis and the existing
core team from Kolla.  This will improve information transfer and
training of the existing core team for Mesos.  The short term goal
will be to retire this group and move the folks into the main
kolla-core team once they have met our informal requirements for
review output and quality, IRC participation, code generation, etc.

To avoid any code dump, this will be a fresh cookiecutter repository
that Angus will merge with project-config separately.

Change-Id: I902d4c31c13d4941a470553e8013ac7692462f1a
'}]
commit_message:
Add kolla-mesos deliverable repo to Kolla

The kolla-mesos repository was majority voted accepted by the core
reviewer team of Kolla to be adopted into the Kolla governance.
The purpose of this repository is to orchestrate a Kolla deployment
in addition to Ansible but instead with Mesos.  If this experiment
fails, the repository will be filed in the attic.

The core reviewer team has committed to reviewing the changes for
this repository and learning how mesos operates.  Angus Salkeld
of Mirantis has committed 4 full time engineers to work on this
project.

The structure of the governance will be the addition of a team
kolla-mesos-core with only 2 people from Mirantis and the existing
core team from Kolla.  This will improve information transfer and
training of the existing core team for Mesos.  The short term goal
will be to retire this group and move the folks into the main
kolla-core team once they have met our informal requirements for
review output and quality, IRC participation, code generation, etc.

To avoid any code dump, this will be a fresh cookiecutter repository
that Angus will merge with project-config separately.

Change-Id: I902d4c31c13d4941a470553e8013ac7692462f1a

Exclude all BDM checks for cells

Since there are some race conditions with the EBS image checking test,
it's better to remove the entire Tempest class tests just until we
figure out what's wrong with the boot from volume stuff

Related-Bug: #1489581

commit_message:
Fix attibute error when cloning raw images in Ceph

A regression introduced in If03b166d3ecc3e7fa6b7f1a0c69f8ab1cc7b1972
causes a glance image with the type 'raw' in ceph to fail to CoW
clone which prevents launching at all in this case.

The original patch did not update imagebackend.py [1] to use the new
nova.objects.ImageMeta object so the clone() function passes a normal
dict to the is_cloneable() function.

Additionally add another test to ensure that not passing disk_format
will fail, but not result in an exception. It will simply mean that
the function returns that it cannot take advantage of the CoW cloning
ceph provides.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/f2e2a5891d5f5ff9346e6dc8e4dd0e994485245c/nova/virt/libvirt/imagebackend.py#L824

Change-Id: I7ae107bfccab7ff66c09d96856722dd6e60fdd96
Closes-Bug: #1508230

commit_message:
SAML2 authentication plugins in keystoneauth

Move SAML2 related auth plugins directly to keystoneauth.
Since SAML2 plugins requires ``lxml` which is a heavy dependency,
plugins will be installed on request:

$ pip install keystoneauth[saml2]

Authentication plugins has been renamed to Saml2Password
and ADFSPassword.

Change-Id: I7872f7524902e4b723ab685c684e16162a4af781
Implements: bp saml2-to-ksa

commit_message:
Add --force to grub-install

Grub fails to install the bootloader due to it being on the root
partition of a block device. This is not actually a problem for us, so
we need to force it to succeed.

Change-Id: I335ef04ca8a8a8a5c242d3444b09bcce0a9f51e7

commit_message:
Don't use default=None for config options

In the config module default=None is set as the default value,
so it isn't necessary to set it again when doing config options.

Change-Id: I09989ab679d249a9f7dea6af5d53c14dd1726e09
Closes-Bug: #1323975

Magnum k8s functional testing will try to access m-api inside of a VM, the
default setting of SERVICE_HOST is 127.0.0.1 which is not accessable from VM.

This patch uses eth0's ip addr as SERVICE_HOST

Closes-Bug: #1514286
Change-Id: I7f3980896d36a6683e364efa6f78563f10990ecd
"}]
commit_message:
Magnum: set SERVICE_HOST to eth0's ip address

Magnum k8s functional testing will try to access m-api inside of a VM, the
default setting of SERVICE_HOST is 127.0.0.1 which is not accessable from VM.

This patch uses eth0's ip addr as SERVICE_HOST

Closes-Bug: #1514286
Change-Id: I7f3980896d36a6683e364efa6f78563f10990ecd

commit_message:
Change method to get the user_id

Instead of "find_project", using "find_user" to get the user_id
while the option --user is specified for "openstack volume list"

[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-10-22 18:00:17.000000000', 'files': ['nova/tests/unit/objects/test_image_meta.py', 'nova/objects/image_meta.py'], 'message': "Fix missing obj_make_compatible() for ImageMetaProps object

This object was never added with an obj_make_compatible() handler for
the many versions we've had since its introduction. This adds that,
rules for the existing versions, and a test for the future.

Note that version 1.6 added values to an enum, so this validates that
an exception is raised during backporting if that field has a value
that would be invalid for the requested version.

Change-Id: I64d40b6fe5e738cf32537c73b9fec57a7fbcdf2d
"}]
commit_message:
Fix missing obj_make_compatible() for ImageMetaProps object

This object was never added with an obj_make_compatible() handler for
the many versions we've had since its introduction. This adds that,
rules for the existing versions, and a test for the future.

Note that version 1.6 added values to an enum, so this validates that
an exception is raised during backporting if that field has a value
that would be invalid for the requested version.

Change-Id: I64d40b6fe5e738cf32537c73b9fec57a7fbcdf2d

commit_message:
Remove flavors.get_all_flavors() only used in tests

This method is only used in tests, sometimes even in orphaned code.
This method really just calls the object method FlavorList.get_all()
and wraps the result in a dict.

Lets remove it an replace the few remaining places where it actually
was used with direct calls to the object method.

Change-Id: I990f81af3d24a5b98d1905d44262c138fd2a0283
